guidelines/http/methods.rst.message:
This is too absolute. You should clarify that DELETE on a bad URI should return a 404. That is:

    DELETE /resource_providers/{uuid}

should never 404, it should be idempotent as described. But:

    DELETE /resource_provider/{uuid}

_should_ 404 because there is no possible entity at that URI at no point in time in the past or future.
